The paper deals with fair division, a topic that falls under the category of computational social choice (cs.GT). The use of a social network to model the agents' preferences suggests that the paper could also be classified under social and information networks (cs.SI). The paper also involves algorithms and complexity analysis, which could place it under data structures and algorithms (cs.DS) or artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the paper's focus on envy-freeness and proportionality suggests that it could be classified under social choice theory (cs.SOC).
